    {
      "name": "3️⃣ Google Auth — Valid ID Token",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"idToken\": \"PASTE_REAL_GOOGLE_ID_TOKEN_HERE\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/google",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "auth", "google"]
        },
        "description": "**Expected:** 200 OK (existing user) or 201 Created (new user)\n\n**How to get a real Google ID token for testing:**\n1. In your frontend app, use `@react-oauth/google` or the Google Sign-In JS SDK\n2. On successful Google sign-in, you get an `idToken` (also called `credential`)\n3. Copy that token here\n\n**Quick test method (browser console):**\n```js\ngoogle.accounts.id.initialize({\n  client_id: 'YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID',\n  callback: (res) => console.log(res.credential) // This is your idToken\n});\n```\n\n**Note:** ID tokens expire in ~1 hour. You need a fresh one each test session."
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Google auth returns 200 or 201', () => {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Response has tokens', () => {",
              "  const body = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (body.success) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', body.data.accessToken);",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', body.data.refreshToken);",
              "    console.log('isNewUser:', body.data.isNewUser);",
              "  }",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
